advisory.title: Arbitrary File Overwrite
advisory.overview: Versions of `fstream` prior to 1.0.12 are vulnerable to Arbitrary File Overwrite. Extracting tarballs containing a hardlink to a file that already exists in the system and a file that matches the hardlink will overwrite the system's file with the contents of the extracted file. The `fstream.DirWriter()` function is vulnerable.
advisory.recommendation: Upgrade to version 1.0.12 or later.

advisory.title: Prototype Pollution
advisory.overview: Versions of `set-value` prior to 3.0.1 or 2.0.1 are vulnerable to Prototype Pollution. The `set` function fails to validate which Object properties it updates. This allows attackers to modify the prototype of Object, causing the addition or modification of an existing property on all objects.
advisory.recommendation:
If you are using `set-value` 3.x, upgrade to version 3.0.1 or later.
If you are using `set-value` 2.x, upgrade to version 2.0.1 or later.

advisory.title: Prototype Pollution
advisory.overview: Versions of `handlebars` prior to are vulnerable to Prototype Pollution leading to Remote Code Execution. Templates may alter an Objects' `__proto__` and `__defineGetter__` properties, which may allow an attacker to execute arbitrary code through crafted payloads.
advisory.recommendation: Upgrade to version 4.3.0 or later.

advisory.title: Machine-In-The-Middle
advisory.overview: Versions of `https-proxy-agent` prior to 2.2.3 are vulnerable to Machine-In-The-Middle. The package fails to enforce TLS on the socket if the proxy server responds the to the request with a HTTP status different than 200. This allows an attacker with access to the proxy server to intercept unencrypted communications, which may include sensitive information such as credentials.
advisory.recommendation: Upgrade to version 3.0.0 or 2.2.3.

advisory.title: Regular Expression Denial of Service
advisory.overview: Versions of `braces` prior to 2.3.1 are vulnerable to Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS). Untrusted input may cause catastrophic backtracking while matching regular expressions. This can cause the application to be unresponsive leading to Denial of Service.
advisory.recommendation: Upgrade to version 2.3.1 or higher.
